04/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the BiH presidency met with High Representative Paddy Ashdown on Monday (3 November) about a bill establishing a joint security and intelligence unit in the two entities.
The two institutions supported calls for a single organisation, saying it would be consistent with the European standards.
In other news Monday, Ashdown reiterated that authorities must agree on reforms of the Pubic Broadcasting System by Friday, or face the loss of 1.5m euros in grants pledged by the EU.
(Dnevni Avaz, Oslobodjenje - 04/11/03;
BHTV, RTRS, FTV - 03/11/03)
